Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.01,0:00:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David Hawkins. I've been a psychiatrist for 35 years, psychoanalyst, physician, researcher\Nand the relationship between nutrition and the relationship to alcoholism and addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.80,0:00:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for the last 10 years doing research into the nature of consciousness itself and its\Nrelationship to that which is called spiritual. And today's talk is going to be on understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.22,0:00:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of addiction, letting go of alcoholism and addiction. And we'll be presenting this\Nwhole topic of alcoholism and addiction from the viewpoint of consciousness itself, a different
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.82,0:00:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,way of approaching the topic, a way of discerning what is the essential nature of the addictive\Nprocess rather than what are its consequences or its physical correlates. We'll be talking
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.86,0:00:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,about the nature of consciousness itself and how...\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.22,0:01:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So understanding of this will give us a different context in which to understand the addictive\Nprocess and its relationship to human behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.40,0:01:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll be looking today at a map of consciousness, one that we've used in this series of talks\Nand one which we have found has been very useful in research and making understandable
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.52,0:01:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that which hitherto for has been perhaps considered mystical.\NIt's been considered mystical, or esoteric, or too right-brained for a left-brained people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.86,0:01:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand.\NAnd so on the blackboard here we have what looks complicated but actually is quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.47,0:01:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The various levels of consciousness and these levels as you can see have been calibrated.\NSo out of the research we've done, for instance, we have calibrated the relative power of these
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.39,0:02:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,energy fields and their direction. And we will begin to understand a lot of human behavior.\NAnd out of that we'll understand the addictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.97,0:02:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In this calibration you'll notice where death is calibrated at zero, if death is calibrated\Nat zero, then we will find an enlightenment, or leaving the world of duality, transcending
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.63,0:02:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,limitation calibrates at about 600.\NWe notice that the energy field of courage is at 200, pride 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.43,0:02:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll refer back to these numbers in the course of our discussion. Importantly also we'll notice that\Nthe direction of these arrows shows whether it is a negative energy field, that which
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.61,0:02:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is not inimicable to life, or whether it's a positive energy field, that which is supportive\Nto life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.54,0:02:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In understanding addiction then, we need to understand the nature of consciousness itself\Nfirst, and then we'll go back to how this applies to the addictive process. We'll look
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.72,0:02:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,at what is the true nature of addiction, and what is the quality that society has missed,\Nbecause society's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.03,0:03:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of addiction has not been very successful. Until the advent of Alcoholics\NAnonymous, let us say, society's recovery rate from the addictions was zero. It was
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.91,0:03:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,never heard of that anybody ever recovered from alcoholism, and it was only the truth\Nas represented by Carl Jung, who said that science alone has no answer for this problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.13,0:03:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that something\Nover-ambiguously
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.93,0:03:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond ordinary human experience, meaning within the limitations of science, has to\Nbe sought, and there the answer will be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.11,0:03:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And that brings in then spirituality, and what does that mean? We'll be talking about\Nthe relationship between body, mind, and spirit. What is the relationship between body, mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.76,0:04:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and spirit? And what is spirit anyway? Is it some kind of a mythical entity? Is it a\Nmetaphysical fantasy? What is the nature of spirit, and how does it operate in a real
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.87,0:04:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,way that we can verify through our own clinical experience?\NSo we won't be talking about philosophy. We won't be talking about epistemology. We're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.61,0:04:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be talking about that which you can verify for yourself through your own inner\Nexperience, and truth as it can be experienced within yourself, and then how this is going
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.41,0:04:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to be applied.\NSo today we'll be talking about the understanding of alcoholism and the addictions, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.23,0:04:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,importance thereof in their recovery.\NAnd so today we'll be talking about context. The overall way in which you hold a thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.11,0:04:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the space from which you're coming, how to be with a subject, because it's context\Nthat creates all of meaning. It's context that defines goal, and coming from a context
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.69,0:04:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of understanding\Na day
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.29,0:05:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll go to this map today, and we'll start explaining it. Within the box here is\Nthe ego, the ego, that which is called the self with a small s. And within the ego we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.79,0:05:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,see we have these different energy fields which we mentioned before. Starting at the\Nbottom, then, we have an energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.09,0:05:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This energy field is called guilt. And you'll notice over to the right of these energy fields\Nis an emotion, an emotion, how we experience this energy field in our daily life. And to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.17,0:05:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the right of that we'll notice a process, the process which is going on within consciousness\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.50,0:05:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That energy field will also determine how we experience and see the world, how we see\Nthe world, and how we would relate to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:06:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of our understanding, because of the limitation of our own energy fields.\NAnd starting at the bottom, as we said, is an energy field called guilt. And we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.17,0:06:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it is calibrated with 30, using death as zero, 30 then, is a state of, really a state of\Ndestruction. And it's experienced usually in the form of self-hatred. And the world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.35,0:06:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is seen as a place of sin and suffering. And God is really the ultimate, the ultimate, the\Nthreat or destroyer of the soul, because he will throw the soul into destruction, into
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.83,0:06:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,hellfire forever.\NSo this is really the lowest energy field, and one with very little power in it. And
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.97,0:06:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,when we move up to the next one, we move up to an energy field of hopelessness and despair,\Nwhich is calibrated at 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.77,0:06:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopelessness and despair means, for instance, like the old lady rocking back and forth in\Nher rocking chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.31,0:07:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She's staring out the window, and she got a notice from the State Department that her\Nson was killed in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.43,0:07:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, the family shakes her, you know, and tries to get her to respond, and she doesn't\Nrespond to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.49,0:07:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because accompanying these energy fields, there's changes in brain chemistry. There's\Nbeen a happening now within her neurotransmitters, within her brain, and so that she doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.23,0:07:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,respond.\NSo hopelessness and despair represents a process going on within her brain, and so that she
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.23,0:07:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't respond.\NSo hopelessness and despair represents a process going on within her brain, and so that she
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.23,0:07:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't respond.\NSo hopelessness and despair represents a process going on in consciousness of loss of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.54,0:07:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is seen as hopeless, and if there is a God, he would have nothing to do with\Nyou, because your own self-esteem is so low that God wouldn't want anything to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.58,0:07:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a worm like yourself.\NSo we call it sort of the worm view of the nature of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.57,0:08:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get the person out of that very low energy field, we can get them up to a higher\Nenergy field called grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.25,0:08:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in hopelessness cannot help themself, and we have to pour energy into them, and\Nif we can, we can get them up perhaps to this energy field called grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.37,0:08:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief calibrates at 75.\NIt has a lot more energy than hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.33,0:08:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief has a certain biologic purpose.\NIn other words, the child, when it cries, summons the mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.79,0:08:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the power to pull some kind of response from the world.\NIt has the power to pull some kind of response from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.25,0:08:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the power to pull some kind of response from the world.\NAnd the emotion that accompanies grief is one of regret, a feeling of loss, a feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.47,0:08:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of despondency.\NAnd we see the process going on in consciousness is dispirited, spirit being that high energy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.95,0:08:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which all of life is a manifestation.\NThe person in grief then sees this as a very sad world and an unloving God who doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.24,0:09:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,really care for you.\NAnd it is a very sad world and an unloving God who doesn't really care for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.37,0:09:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if we have the old lady rocking back and forth in her rocking chair and not eating\Nand not responding, and let's say we get a telegram from the State Department that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.39,0:09:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,says the previous telegram was a mistake.\NIt was really someone else with a different name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.49,0:09:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the family gathers around to her and they say, mother, mother, it wasn't Joey that got\Nkilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.49,0:09:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all a mistake.\NHe's alive and well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.49,0:09:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And she goes right on rocking back and forth.\NStill standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.37,0:09:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Still standing there.\NStill standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.59,0:09:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Still standing there.\NStill standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.73,0:09:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,She's down there.\NShe's down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.83,0:09:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She's down there.\NShe's down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.05,0:09:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She's down there.\NShe's down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.21,0:09:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,staring out the window.\NIf we could get that woman now by pouring energy into her up to a level of grief, all
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.44,0:09:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of a sudden she begins to cry.\NThe expression of that emotion now indicates to us that she is getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.49,0:09:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Interestingly enough, these two energy states come out of the failure to face the energy\Nfield which lies just above it called fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.58,0:10:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field of fear, still a negative emotion as you can see by the direction of\Nthe arrow, but an energy field now of 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.14,0:10:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,100 is a lot of energy.\NYou see, you can run a long way out of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.88,0:10:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the emotion itself, the form of the emotion is not constructive, but the energy out of\Nit can be utilized in a very positive way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.48,0:10:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And so all these energy fields have their upside and their downside.\NThe downside which can be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.68,0:10:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Negatively, the upside, if you know how to utilize it, you can utilize the energy of\Nfear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.60,0:10:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you know what to be afraid of, it can be a very constructive thing in your life.\NFear as we ordinarily experience it in ordinary life is experienced as worry, anxiety, panic,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.26,0:10:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually even terror.\NSo grief, you see, has to do with the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.14,0:10:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief has to do with the past.\NAnd fear has to do with the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.14,0:11:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The process going on.\NConsciousness is one of deflation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.64,0:11:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The fearful animal shrinks and hides.\NWhen you're in third grade and the teacher asks for a response to a question, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.50,0:11:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,how we used to shrink and hide behind the person in front of us.\NSo we shrink and become deflated less than that which we are in fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.14,0:11:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And the kind of world that we see, our perception of the world that comes out of this energy\Nfield is that this is a frightening and threatening world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.74,0:11:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,See how we can take away from the world.\NAnd who is the god of a frightening and threatening world?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.02,0:11:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A very punitive god.\NAnd so, god is seen as a punisher, and much to be feared.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.12,0:11:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the holding of all the sense of sin and guilt, and low self-esteem in this\Nlevel of consciousness, holds god as the most frightening of all possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.00,0:12:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving a person out of fear.\NYou're able to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.30,0:12:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,up to the next energy field, which we call desire, and desire at 125, as you know, has\Nan awful lot of energy, desiring to want.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.96,0:12:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So its expression in our ordinary emotion is that of wanting and craving.\NThat can eventually become an obsession, a compulsion, and we then call it an addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.98,0:12:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And why is this so?\NBecause the process going on in consciousness is one of entrapment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.40,0:12:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The person has become entrapped.\NThey are at the effect of, they are run by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.82,0:12:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the marketing industry, of course, this is their purpose, to create in you, to\Nplay off your desires, to create a wanting and a craving, to get you entrapped to want
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,their product.\NOnce you become entrapped by that, whether it's a fancy car or a certain perfume or a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.52,0:13:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,shampoo that's going to make you lovely, whatever, then that will run you.\Nand you'd be willing to give up your money and your energy and buy their product.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.00,0:13:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Desiringness, however, leads to a world because of the endless wantingness of this\Ncoming out of your solar plexus of a very frustrating world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.94,0:13:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difficulty with wantingness is though it can drive you,\Nthe wanting a Ph.D., the wanting to be a doctor, the wanting to live in a good address.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.34,0:13:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All these wantings, which can run us for an entire lifetime,\Nlead to a certain sense of frustration because wantingness does not cure itself by getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.94,0:13:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It just leads to additional wantingness.\NYou see, after you finally get a yacht, you will find that as you tie it up,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.41,0:13:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody next to you has a bigger yacht.\NAnd so the wantingness in and of itself is not satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.87,0:13:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this constant frustration leads to a picture of God from whom you're separated.\NIn other words, He's the God who forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.61,0:14:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,who never withholds from you what you want.\NAnd it leads easily to anger, which is our next level.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.68,0:14:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger, at 150, as everyone is aware, of course, leads to, has a great deal of energy in it.\NAs you see, it's still a negative emotion and it has a destructive downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.70,0:14:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But the energy of anger, if you know how to use it, it can be a very useful thing.\NWe experience the energy of anger, you know, in every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.44,0:14:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Life, in the emotions of resentment, of feeling hatred, grievances, grudges,\Nthe unwillingness to forgive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.30,0:14:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that what's happened in the process in consciousness is one of expansion.\NThe angry animal swells up with anger, becomes larger than life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.18,0:14:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who's angry, their veins swell, they swell up with this angriness\Nand try to become imposing on the biologic level, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.00,0:15:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This angriness, then, leads to a competitiveness.\NThe angry person sees a world of competition, of conflict, of war, of me against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.60,0:15:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a polarized position of opponents.\NAnd therefore, the God, understand, the view of God that comes out of that is an angry God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.85,0:15:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person who sees God is the ultimate,\Nultimate anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.19,0:15:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of angriness, the God of vengeance, the God who gets even.\NHe's the God who's coming out of his spleen, is he not?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.33,0:15:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He's coming out of a revenge, a hatred, an anger.\NIt's as though he now hates that which he created
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.43,0:15:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and hates the humanness of that which he created.\NThe God of retaliatory, vengeful angriness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.98,0:16:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If we move up out of this angriness, if we can move up to pride,\Nwe see that pride has an energy field of 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.92,0:16:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lot of power.\NAnd pride is enough to energize the United States Marine Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.92,0:16:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride can be a very useful emotion.\NThe difficulty with pride, because we see the energy field of it is still in a negative direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the emotions experienced with pride, the downside of it is denial.\NAnd in the addictions, of course, this is very, can be very fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.37,0:16:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NDenial, taking the form of arrogance and contempt, saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.87,0:16:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,well, it's good, you know, those people need it, but not me, I'm different.\NAnd that comes out of the fact that the process going on in consciousness is one of inflated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.87,0:16:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The person is coming from an inflated sense of self, a very dangerous position,\Nand therefore we see the pridefulness which leads to the destruction eventually,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.87,0:17:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the rapid destruction, coming down to destruction.\NIn the rock stars and people who get into drugs who are successful very early in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.87,0:17:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this enormous inflation of the ego, the denial that goes with it,\Nthe contempt for the valuation of life, the inability to hear the advice of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.96,0:17:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So pridefulness leads us to then a very vulnerable defensiveness.\NIt is not a good position to be in,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.96,0:17:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's an energy field.\NIt's an energy that we can utilize when we're moving ourselves from anger up to courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.51,0:17:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, out of this energy field of pride.\NThe person in pride then is very preoccupied with status, with ownership,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with havingness, with symbols, with labels.\NAnd it's a very defensive position to be in, this preoccupation with status.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.50,0:18:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that energy field, which comes out as denial, arrogance,\Ncontempt, an inflated energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.66,0:18:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,how does that influence our viewpoint of God?\NThe relationship to God then would be one of usually two possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.85,0:18:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the arrogance of the intellect, out of the left brainness,\Nthe presumption that the left brain has the capacity to know all of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,could come a position of atheism.\NAnd the position of atheism then is a denial,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.81,0:18:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a denial of the truth of which can be experienced through human experience.\NOr it could take its opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.16,0:18:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It could take the form of bigotry.\NIt could take the form of the religionist,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.16,0:18:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who takes the position then that my way of seeing things is the only way,\Nand because my way is the truth, your way, therefore, is not the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.16,0:19:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So pride is a position which polarizes us,\Nin which everybody else then becomes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.16,0:19:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,see there's our position, which is correct,\Nand therefore everybody else's position is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.16,0:19:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So pridefulness then is a polarizing position of me against you,\Nand of course it is the basis of all the religious wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.52,0:19:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride has a useful energy in it, as the Marine Corps has found out.\NAnd it's useful to us to move on through to a higher energy field called courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.06,0:19:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now courage is a very crucial level to us.\NAnd crucial because you see, for one thing, the arrow now suddenly goes neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.06,0:19:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the energy field of that level of consciousness is now shifted to neutral.\NIt's as though the negative antenna, the antenna which was tuned to negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.06,0:19:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is now tuned to neutral.\NIt stops pulling to itself in experience that which is negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.06,0:20:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Its energy field is 200, which is a lot of power.\NSo courage has enough energy in it, you know, to settle the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.48,0:20:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage has enough to get a man to the moon.\NIt has enough to establish all of science,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.48,0:20:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to explore intellectual frontiers of philosophy.\NSo courage at 200 is enough to create all the great industrial empires.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.51,0:20:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a very powerful energy field,\Nnot because it jumped another 25 points,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.08,0:20:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but because now the direction of the field has changed.\NMuch of that resistance has dropped off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.08,0:20:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the first time now, the person emotionally is able to face,\Nto cope, to handle, to look at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.08,0:20:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the critical thing that happens in consciousness,\Nthe process going on in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.08,0:20:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the person becomes empowered.\NThe person becomes empowered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.08,0:20:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And what made this huge jump?\NWhat made this huge jump in power?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.08,0:21:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What crosses the line and makes you go beyond that level\Nis the willingness to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.47,0:21:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to tell the truth.\NThis is going to be crucial in the understanding of the addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.47,0:21:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and the understanding of the traditional 12 steps.\NBecause it is in the first step,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.47,0:21:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the admission that one is powerless over alcohol and drugs,\Nthat it is making our life unbearable,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.47,0:21:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that changes this entire energy field\Nand re-empowers the person now
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.47,0:21:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and puts them in a position of recovery.\NWhat kind of view of the world takes place
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.33,0:21:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from this energy field of courage\Nwhen you start telling the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.33,0:21:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to see this as a world of opportunity.\NYou see it as a world of challenge,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.33,0:21:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a very exciting world\Nin which to grow and experience one's growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of a view of God comes about now?\NThese were all below the line of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.33,0:22:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If we tested them all with kinesiology,\Nwe find that you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.33,0:22:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them are denials of the truth.\NOut of this energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.33,0:22:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of view of God opens up\Nis the open mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.33,0:22:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time, the person really tells the truth.\NThe truth is that through one's own experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.33,0:22:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,one has not really had an experience\Nof what there is called God within the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.33,0:22:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, through that question mark then,\Nfor the first time, the mind is open.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.33,0:22:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The person begins to ask the traditional questions\Nwhich have always led to the ultimate realization
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.33,0:22:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of the truth of that question.\NIs there a God? Is He experienced?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.33,0:22:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Can it be experienced?\NIs it something I can verify within myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.75,0:22:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is God something out there or within me?\NHow does it express itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.75,0:22:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I get to know that?\NThe whole spiritual exploration begins then
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.75,0:22:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,with the beginning of integrity,\Nbecause this is the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.75,0:23:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of the first level of integrity, of empowerment.\NThe capacity to tell the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.75,0:23:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which gives us the power,\Ngives us the power to face and cope and handle
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.75,0:23:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the first time be appropriate.\NOut of the energy field of courage then,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.55,0:23:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to look at the facts\Nand admit the truth about them,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.55,0:23:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we can move to the next energy field\Nwhich is called neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.55,0:23:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here you see the arrow now\Nis positively going to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.55,0:23:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field has jumped to two levels.\NIt's at 250.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.64,0:23:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And how is that level experienced?\NThat's experienced as being unattached.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.64,0:23:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've told the truth about a thing,\Nyou may move up to a process
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.68,0:23:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in which we call released,\Nin which you're no longer attached to outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.71,0:23:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what is a person like\Non this energy field of neutral?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.71,0:23:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're in a state, we would say,\Nit's okay either way it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.71,0:24:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person on this energy level then would say,\Nwell, if I get the job, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.71,0:24:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I don't get the job, that's okay too\Nbecause I'll just find another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.71,0:24:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if this relationship doesn't work out,\Nwell, then I'll find another relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.84,0:24:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there's the experience then\Nof the okayness of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.84,0:24:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and a sense of God as being\Nthe source of freedom,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.84,0:24:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the freedom to grow and expand\Nand become conscious
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.84,0:24:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and to begin to look into oneself\Nand the nature of human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.84,0:24:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A God who looks favorably then\Non the exploration of your own consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.35,0:24:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So neutral is unattached.\NThe downside of neutral would be sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.35,0:24:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,flat and indifferent, flat and indifferent.\NThe upside of it, we could move in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.35,0:24:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to a state called willingness.\NWillingness, which calibrates out at about 310,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.35,0:24:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,then has a lot more power and energy\Nbecause for the first time intention comes in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.35,0:25:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have said yes.\NWe say yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.35,0:25:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A person on the neutral level is sort of like\Nthere's no enthusiasm there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.35,0:25:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to go to the movie,\Nokay, we'll go to the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.35,0:25:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to go to the movie,\Nall right, we'll stay home.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.35,0:25:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not much positive there yet.\NWe've let go of the negative
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.35,0:25:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and by letting go of the negative,\Nwe've created a space for willingness to come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.35,0:25:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So when willingness come in, on the other hand,\Nnow we have the beginning of enthusiasm,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.35,0:25:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of a positive energy.\NWe say yes, we're agreeable, we're willing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.35,0:25:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So this willingness now takes us out of\Nindifference, flatness and detachment
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.83,0:25:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and we begin to experience this as a friendly world.\NThe whole question of God and of life itself
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.83,0:25:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes promising and hopeful\Nbecause we're now saying yes to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.83,0:25:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,See, this person is detached from life.\NThis person is willing to face
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.83,0:25:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and cope.\NThese people don't experience what life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.83,0:26:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They're only experiencing attitudes and belief systems\Nwhich are resisting and negative to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.83,0:26:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the energy field of the arrow\Nis really opposed to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.83,0:26:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,opposed to the truth of life.\NSo willingness then brings us,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.53,0:26:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the next step out of willingness\Nis to move up to acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.53,0:26:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Acceptance calibrates at 380\Nand then a person there is adequate
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.53,0:26:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and confident, capable.\NWe have the beginning of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.53,0:26:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the transformation of consciousness.\NAnd what's bringing about
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.53,0:26:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,this transformation of consciousness\Nis that the person is beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.53,0:26:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to reown their own power.\NAll these fields from courage on down
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.01,0:26:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,are all conditions of victim\Nin which the person has sold out
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.01,0:26:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of their power\Nand given it away to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.01,0:26:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to be extremely important\Nas we look at the addictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.01,0:26:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The giving away of one's power\Nto that which is outside
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.01,0:27:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of oneself which brings about\Nthis negative energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.30,0:27:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who is moving into acceptance\Nnow is reowning that I am the source
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.30,0:27:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of happiness in my life.\NThese people all think that happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.30,0:27:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,lies outside of yourself.\NThey think that happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.30,0:27:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,comes about through getting.\NThese are all conditions of lack
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.30,0:27:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in which if I get that car,\Nif I get that title,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.30,0:27:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if I get that job,\Nif I get that relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.30,0:27:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if I get that degree,\Nif I get that money,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.36,0:27:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever it is,\Nit's always outside of oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.36,0:27:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course in the addictions,\Nif I get that drug
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.36,0:27:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or if I get the right dose of that drug.\NThe thought that the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.36,0:27:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is outside of yourself\Nis what accompanies all these states
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.36,0:27:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of weakness and victimhood.\NThe person on the level of acceptance
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.36,0:27:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,has through the willingness now,\Nthe letting go of the resistance,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.36,0:27:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to begin to accept\Nthat I am the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.36,0:27:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in my life.\NNo matter where you put me,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.36,0:28:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I will recreate something\Nthat satisfies me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.36,0:28:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that person is not coming\Nfrom powerlessness or victimhood now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.36,0:28:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That person knows that if you put them\Non a desert island someplace
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.74,0:28:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and you come back a year later,\Nyou know you'll have
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.74,0:28:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a coconut factory going,\Nyou'll have a tree house
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.74,0:28:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,built in the tree,\Nyou'll be teaching French
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.74,0:28:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to the natives,\Nyou'll find a native girl
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.74,0:28:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who started a new family all over.\NThat power then to recreate
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.16,0:28:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for yourself,\Nthe person who is putting
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.44,0:28:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you in prison let's say.\NYou know what's happening in prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.44,0:28:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At one hand you have suicide.\NOn the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.44,0:28:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you have people who have written\Ngreat prize winning novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.44,0:28:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People who have changed the course\Nof all human history,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.44,0:28:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,have written these incredible\Nand powerful and brilliant books
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.44,0:28:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,while in prison.\NSo it isn't,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.44,0:28:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the power is not in the prison,\Nthe power is in the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.44,0:28:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So the capacity then to use\Neven the prison experience
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.44,0:28:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in a valuable and positive way\Nto create a great novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.44,0:29:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a great book,\Na political treatise.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.24,0:29:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the greatest things\Never written were written
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.24,0:29:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,under conditions that the person\Ndown here would see as impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.24,0:29:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The acceptance that you are the source\Nthen makes this seem like
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.24,0:29:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a harmonious world.\NThat you are the source
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.24,0:29:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of happiness within your world.\NAnd the view of God
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.24,0:29:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes out of this\Npromising hopeful view
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.24,0:29:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is of course the beginning\Nof the merciful God.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.28,0:29:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of mercy,\Nthe God of forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.28,0:29:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as you move up into\Nthe energy field of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.28,0:29:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of acceptance,\Nout of the owning of the power
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.47,0:29:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you are,\Nmoving more towards truth
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.47,0:29:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is the willingness now\Nto become truly loving
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.47,0:29:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and we move up to now\Na powerful energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.47,0:29:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,a plus 500,\Nthe energy field of love itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.69,0:29:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where happiness begins.\NHappiness when you calibrate it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.69,0:29:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,begins at an energy field of 500.\NSo you can see why
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.69,0:29:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,more and more of gettingness,\Nwhich is down in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.69,0:30:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,getting money, sex, power,\Npositions, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.69,0:30:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,does not bring happiness.\NIt brings pleasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.69,0:30:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,brings momentary fulfillment.\NYou can see why
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.69,0:30:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,if 50 million won't make you happy,\Nwhy 75 won't either.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.69,0:30:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because more millions\Nis only a 200 energy field experience
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.69,0:30:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and happiness begins at 500.\NThe beginning then
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.24,0:30:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field of love\Nand what kind of love
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.24,0:30:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are we talking about?\NWe are talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.24,0:30:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional love.\NWe are talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.24,0:30:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a stable energy field\Nwhich nurtures,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.24,0:30:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which supports,\Nout of which comes forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.24,0:30:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of it also becomes\Nthe beginning of revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.24,0:30:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation into the truth of life\Nand this is due to the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.24,0:30:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that within the brain\Nat an energy field of 500
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.24,0:30:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially at 540,\Nthere is the release of endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.24,0:30:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning real alteration,\Nthe correlation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.24,0:30:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,on the physical level\Nwithin the brain chemistry itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.24,0:31:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The view of the world\Ncoming out of this lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.30,0:31:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of course is a loving world\Nand a God of unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.30,0:31:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and unconditional forgiveness.\NIt's a very important point
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.04,0:31:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for us who are in the addictions\Nto understand this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.04,0:31:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is the energy field\Nof Alcoholics Anonymous,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.04,0:31:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcotics Anonymous,\NOvereaters Anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.04,0:31:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The 12 step groups\Nwhich are based on spiritual principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.04,0:31:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate out at an energy field\Nof about 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.04,0:31:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,540 is a critical level\Nbecause the energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.23,0:31:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the level of healing\Nis 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.23,0:31:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,An energy field of 540\Nin and of the nature of that field
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.23,0:31:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is a healing field,\None which is unconditionally loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.32,0:31:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This represents then\Na commitment, an alignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.32,0:31:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This forgivingness becomes automatic\Nbecause out of the revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.03,0:32:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the kind of a world\Nwhich is revealed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.03,0:32:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What's revealed to you\Nis that what is important
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.03,0:32:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is to understand\Nand out of that understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.03,0:32:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually move up\Nto levels of compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.03,0:32:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to understand,\Nthe desire to understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.03,0:32:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that becomes foremost in the mind\Nis revealed as what is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.03,0:32:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The person has a fractured hip,\Nit is not important
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.54,0:32:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,whether they were right or wrong.\NIs it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.96,0:32:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important is to fix it.\NAnd so lovingness then
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.96,0:32:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes a healingness\Nout of its intention to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.96,0:32:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and to heal out of its understandingness.\NThis is a different energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.56,0:32:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,than the one called love by the world.\NWhat the world calls love
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.56,0:32:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of sentimentality.\NIt's coming out of a solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.56,0:32:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalism.\NSo when we hear somebody say,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.56,0:32:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,well I used to love Joey\Nbut I don't love him anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.56,0:32:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What they really mean\Nis they never loved Joey.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.56,0:33:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What they had was a sentimental attachment,\Na dependency,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.56,0:33:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a back and forth control,\Na lustful attachment
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.56,0:33:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,controlling ownership\Nand an emotionality
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.56,0:33:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of their childishness\Nand a feeling of loss
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.56,0:33:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,if that person leaves their life.\NThat which is truly loving
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.56,0:33:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is an inner intention and a commitment\Nso it creates a stable energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.56,0:33:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which never changes.\NIf I decide to love you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.60,0:33:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which is my own intention\Nthen there's nothing you can do about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.60,0:33:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a stable unchanging energy field\Nand we see this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.60,0:33:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see it in the non-judgmentalism\Nof the 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.60,0:33:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Or somebody might have come into a group\Nlet's say who shot three people last week
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.60,0:33:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and ran over some innocent people\Nand what do they say
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.60,0:33:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when he walks into the group meeting?\NThey say, Joe we sure are glad to see you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.60,0:33:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure need us.\NYou sure need us.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.60,0:33:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The unconditionality of that\Nbecause what's being related to now
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.60,0:34:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is the person's beingness.\NWhat's being related to is beingness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.60,0:34:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the love of the true self\Nof what that person really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.60,0:34:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving from the small self\Nwith a small s
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.60,0:34:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,up to the large self\Nwith a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.60,0:34:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the sustaining, nurturing\Nhealing energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.60,0:34:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 12-step groups\Nit's crucial for us to see
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.60,0:34:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that that is the energy\Nthat the energy itself
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.60,0:34:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,irrespective of the personalities.\NAnd so we
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.60,0:34:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you hear in AA the saying\Nyou know, bring the body
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.60,0:34:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll get it by osmosis.\NJust bring the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.60,0:34:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Principle is about personalities.\NIt means that the healing field itself
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.60,0:34:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is what nurtures and supports\Nand brings about the miracle of recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.60,0:34:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the importance then of that alignment\Nwith that energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.60,0:34:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because characteristic of AA\Nis a feeling of gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.60,0:35:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratitude which is at about 540\Nthe value of laughter, of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.60,0:35:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And humor is about 550\Nthe capacity to come from
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.60,0:35:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a different way of holding our experience\Ninstead of self-pity, instead of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.60,0:35:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of anger\Nin its expression as resentment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.60,0:35:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we now hold as humor as that\Nwhich at the time perhaps was tragic.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.20,0:35:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this willingness then\Nto be forgiving, to be understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.20,0:35:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,out of this healing nature of the energy field\Nwe move up to joyful states
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.20,0:35:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,characterized here as compassion.\NThat desire to heal through understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.20,0:35:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to understand\Nwhich brings about the healing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.20,0:35:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of transfiguration\Nin one's consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.20,0:35:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of seeing the perfection of the world\Nexperiencing the oneness of all things
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.20,0:36:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the oneness of all life.\NAs we move up then to 560
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.30,0:36:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which we don't have written on the board\Nwe have an energy field called ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.30,0:36:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,not the jumping up and down\Nkind of emotionalism
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.30,0:36:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but an inner experience of extreme serenity\Nwe move into states
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.30,0:36:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which generically I call bliss.\NThese blissful states
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.30,0:36:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and these blissful states\Nof feelings of expansive well-being
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.30,0:36:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of being at one with everything\Na feeling of generous lovingness and forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.30,0:36:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a feeling of inner extreme pleasure.\NThis blissful state is important
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.07,0:36:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in the understanding of the addictions\Nbecause this experience is the most
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.20,0:36:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,addictive of all human experiences\Naddictive in a generic sense
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.20,0:36:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the terms of the addictions\Nbut that the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.20,0:36:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is possible within oneself\Nthe experience let us say
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.20,0:37:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes out of meditation\Na person studies a meditative technique
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.20,0:37:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and now suddenly they go into an expansive state\Nof infinite oneness and bliss
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.20,0:37:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a state called samadhi.\NFrom this experience of samadhi
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.42,0:37:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the person now is aware of what is possible\Nand then comes into the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.42,0:37:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a desire to return to that state.\NThe knowingness now of what is possible
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.42,0:37:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,creates the desire to return to that\Nand the person's life usually changes
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.42,0:37:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to a considerable degree\Nonce that has been experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.42,0:37:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and many people will leave their lifestyle\Nand shift to a totally different lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.42,0:37:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,directed towards spiritual purification\Nthe removal of all that has obstructed
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.42,0:37:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencing of this state.\NPeople who have had near death experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.52,0:38:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are many books on that now\Nnear death experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.52,0:38:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,where they are declared dead on the operating table\Nthe movie Revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.52,0:38:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,which is about such a person\Nvery clinically accurate
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.52,0:38:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencing of that infinite state\Nof blissfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.52,0:38:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and subsequent to that\Nthe dramatic change in the person's lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.52,0:38:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of that experience now\Nwith a different knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.52,0:38:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a different orientation\Na different context.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.25,0:38:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The movie Lost Horizon\Nwhich has always been one of my favorites
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.25,0:38:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,depicts extremely well the same thing\Nas you remember Ronald Coleman in the original version
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.25,0:38:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,when he falls into Shangri-La\Na state of unconditional lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.25,0:38:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a state which recalibrates\Naround a little over 600
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.25,0:38:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and he experiences this\Nstate of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.73,0:38:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and then when he tries to return\Nto the ordinary world
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.73,0:38:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he returns to a world which\Nrecalibrates around 200
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.73,0:39:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of successful doing this\Nand getting this
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.73,0:39:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he cannot find any satisfaction\Nin this world anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.73,0:39:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to what he has experienced\Nand so there was then
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.73,0:39:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to return\Nto that state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.73,0:39:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that energy field\Nwhich in the movie is depicted as a place
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.73,0:39:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but which we know is actually\Nexperienced within consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.73,0:39:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire at any cost\Nto return to that inner state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.73,0:39:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to look then at where\Nall human experience occurs
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.79,0:39:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said\Nthe body is unable to experience itself
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.79,0:39:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only experienced in mind\Nit is the mind that is experiencing the body
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.79,0:39:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,mind itself\Nis experienced by consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.79,0:39:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise you would not be aware\Nof what is going on within mind
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.79,0:39:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and so experience is taking place then\Nwithin an energy field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.79,0:39:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is this inner experience\Nwithin consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.79,0:40:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of a blissful state\Nto which people become addicted
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.79,0:40:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who have never taken drugs\Nnow what happens then
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.17,0:40:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in the drug experience\Nthis energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.17,0:40:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of life itself\Nlike the sun is always shining
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.17,0:40:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,these energy fields here\Nwe could say are like the clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.72,0:40:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the clouds block off the experience\Nof that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.72,0:40:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,which is ever shining\Nand what a drug does then
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.91,0:40:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is it blocks off our experience\Nof these lower energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.91,0:40:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and allows us to experience\Nthe presence of a higher energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.91,0:40:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,within us\Nif we could block off
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.97,0:40:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,all these energy fields\Nlet's say
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.97,0:40:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,up to the level of 560\Nwhich is the level of ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.97,0:40:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if we could find some way\Nof blocking off all the clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.97,0:40:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,blocking off all these energy fields\Nup to 560
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.97,0:40:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what would we experience\Nwe would experience what's left
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.97,0:41:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is\Nan energy field of ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.97,0:41:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and isn't there such a designer drug\Nand yes indeed
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.97,0:41:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there is one\Ncalled ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.97,0:41:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,designed specifically\Nto block off the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.97,0:41:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of all these energy fields\Nother than 560 or over
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.97,0:41:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and so what's happened then\Nwith the drug experience
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.52,0:41:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is that pharmacologically\Nsomething has blocked off
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.52,0:41:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,this lower energy field\Nand allowed us to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.52,0:41:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,something of a higher energy field\Nso the person coming home
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.52,0:41:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,full of fears and griefs\Nand regrets and anxieties
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.52,0:41:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,stops in for two martinis\Nand now suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.52,0:41:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they jump all these energy fields\Nand they move up to an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.52,0:41:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,at about 500\Nwhat I call mellow
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.52,0:41:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,mellow\Nmellow is that field
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.96,0:41:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,where you sort of love everybody\Nyou're willing to forgive everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.96,0:41:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're generous\Neasy going
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.96,0:41:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the kids love you\Nwhen you're in that state
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.96,0:42:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you bring home toys for the children\Nand flowers for the wife
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.16,0:42:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the energy state\N500 and over
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.57,0:42:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that is sought in the drug experience\Nthe blocking off of that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.57,0:42:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which is below that\Nand allowing the person to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.57,0:42:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that energy field\Nso we said these are
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.67,0:42:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,addicting experiences\Nbecause the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.67,0:42:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,once having experienced it\Nwishes to return
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.67,0:42:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we asked the person\Nwho's ever had an addictive problem
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.67,0:42:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a person who has an alcohol\Nor addictive problem
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.67,0:42:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at what it is\Nthat they are seeking
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.67,0:42:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,look at what is the experience\Nto which they are habituated
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.67,0:42:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to which they return\Nover and over again
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.67,0:42:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what the price\Nand we see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.83,0:42:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that as an inner state\Nas an inner state of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.83,0:42:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that in reality\Nthey don't even care about the drug
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.83,0:42:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the drug was only\Nthe mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.83,0:42:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the way of accessing\Nthe only way that they knew at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.83,0:43:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain way of experiencing\Ntheir being
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.83,0:43:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,their existence\Na pleasurable
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.83,0:43:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,highly energized state\Nand this is what was sought
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.83,0:43:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and if a drug does not block off\Nthese lower energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.83,0:43:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow you to experience\Nthat inner state of blissfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.83,0:43:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,then it is no longer used\Nand it is not called an addicting drug
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.83,0:43:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you see many of the psychological explanations\Nof addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.83,0:43:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,try to present it as though\Nit is a running away
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.83,0:43:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,from these lower experiences\Nthe person is running away from fear
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.83,0:43:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or the person is running away from depression\Nwell we have some excellent drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.21,0:43:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that will handle that\NThorazine for instance
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.21,0:43:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,will knock out your anxiety\Nfor a couple of weeks maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.21,0:43:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't feel nervous\Nuntil the 4th of July
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.21,0:43:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet nobody calls me up\Nand asks for refills
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.21,0:43:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same with antidepressants\Nan antidepressant will move you out
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.21,0:43:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the depression\Nbut nobody calls up
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.21,0:43:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and says that their prescription\Nfor the antidepressant
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.21,0:43:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is filled on the toilet\Nlike they would with Percodan
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.21,0:44:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so the alleviation of the depression then\Nor the alleviation of the anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.21,0:44:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or the fear\Nor the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.21,0:44:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which is well handled\Npharmacologically by traditional medical drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.21,0:44:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,are not good\Nthey are not considered
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.21,0:44:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to be addictive substances\Nwhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.21,0:44:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because they do not block off\Nthese energy fuels high enough
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.21,0:44:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for you to experience this higher state\Nso now we can see
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.21,0:44:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,what the person is addicted to\Nthe person is addicted
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.21,0:44:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to that energy fuel within\Nto that state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.21,0:44:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to return to that\Nand the price they are willing to pay
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.21,0:44:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is all of it\Nbecause what the mind begins to demand
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.21,0:44:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is a return to that experience\Nno matter what the price
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.21,0:44:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the willingness to pay the price\Nincreases with time
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.21,0:44:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so that in the end\Nfinally it will ask for the body itself
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.21,0:44:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it will say\Nif you keep on drinking like that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.21,0:44:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you are going to be dead\Nwithin weeks or months
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.21,0:44:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know what the person does about that\Nthey go across the street to the bartender
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.21,0:45:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,their old pal Joe\Nthey order a martini
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.21,0:45:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they say\Nguess what the doctor told me today
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.21,0:45:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,at that point the bartender orders them a drink\Nfor all good times
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.21,0:45:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they kiss the body goodbye\Nthe willingness to let all of it go
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.21,0:45:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore we see the price that people\Nare willing to pay
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.21,0:45:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for the so called addiction\Nto this state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.21,0:45:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it mystifies people\Nwho have not accessed that level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.21,0:45:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in their drug experience\Nwhy are these people willing to sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.40,0:45:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all of it\Nthey are willing to sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.40,0:45:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all of it\Nto return to this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.40,0:45:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that energy fuel we call bliss\Nnow let's remind ourselves that we see
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.72,0:45:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the same thing going on with people\Nwho have never taken a drug
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.72,0:45:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who by virtue of their destiny\Nor previous spiritual work whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.82,0:45:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have fallen into the energy fuels\Nof these higher experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.04,0:46:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see them do the same thing\Nthe willingness to give up power and money
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.04,0:46:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and position and titles in the world\Nto devote all of their time and energy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.04,0:46:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to the returning\Nto this state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.04,0:46:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore that movie\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.04,0:46:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Lost Horizon\Nreally tells us the whole story of addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.04,0:46:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to sacrifice all of it\Nfor a certain state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.04,0:46:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as though there is an innate inner\Nawareness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.04,0:46:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is really true\Nand there is this false start
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.04,0:46:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience what is true\Nfalse start because it doesn't work
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.04,0:46:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so the reason for the giving up of the addiction\Nthe giving up of the alcohol and drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.04,0:46:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is not because it's wrong\Nnot because it's wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.04,0:46:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but because it doesn't work\Nit doesn't work
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.04,0:46:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because as you move from here\Nup to here what happens is you bring about
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.04,0:46:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as we all know the progressive\Nloss of inner self-respect
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.04,0:47:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the reversities and negativities\Nof these energy fuels the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.04,0:47:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of the experience of\Nnegative experiences in one's life
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.04,0:47:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of the loss of relationships\Nthe loss of credit cards
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.04,0:47:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of status\Nloss of physical health
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.04,0:47:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of the function of the body organs\Nwe see the progressive downhill course
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.04,0:47:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,brought about by the denial of the truth\Nand what is the denial of the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.04,0:47:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that is going on here\Nthe denial of the truth as we said
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.04,0:47:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,everything from this level on down\Nis due to putting the power
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.04,0:47:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of yourself\Nand so we see what's happened in
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.04,0:47:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in the addiction\Nis that the person has given this source
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.04,0:47:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,which these people here accept\Nthe source of their happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.08,0:47:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of meaning in their life\Nhave projected it into the outer world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.11,0:47:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and given that power to the drug\Nthey've given the power
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.11,0:47:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to some substance outside of themselves\Nthe drug in and of itself
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.11,0:47:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,has no power at all\Nto create these higher experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.11,0:48:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we've tested this out in research\Nfor several years
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.11,0:48:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with literally hundreds of people\Nand in the classes we've been giving
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.36,0:48:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance\Npeople who are fighting
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.36,0:48:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and right in the middle of\Nhandling their addictive problem
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.36,0:48:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we've tested with kinesiology\Nthe proposition
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.49,0:48:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the drug has the power\Nto create this higher experience
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.49,0:48:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and universally\N100% of the people go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.49,0:48:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,with that proposition\Nproving that it is a lie
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.49,0:48:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the drug has no power whatsoever\Nand then we present them
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.49,0:48:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,with an opposite concept\Nand we have everybody in the class
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.49,0:48:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,hold in mind its opposite thought\Nthat the drug blocks off
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.49,0:48:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy fields that\Nare coming from that which I am not
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.49,0:48:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow me to experience the joyfulness\Nof that which is my real self
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.49,0:48:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and instantly everybody in the class\Ngoes strong
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.49,0:48:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,indicating that it is the truth\Nso the truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.49,0:48:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the drug has no power\Nto create these experiences whatsoever
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.49,0:49:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it has the pharmacologic capacity\Nto block off these negative energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.62,0:49:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow you to at least\Nget into the ballpark
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.62,0:49:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't the real state of bliss of course\Nof the person who has earned it
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.62,0:49:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,through their own progressive spiritual work\Nbut at least in the ballpark
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.62,0:49:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of what that experience is like\Nto feel that energy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.62,0:49:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,which is closest to\Nthe truth of one's own being
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.45,0:49:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,can we utilize\Nthis knowledge now
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.03,0:49:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in understanding the recovery from addictions\Nwhen the person comes in with an addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.38,0:49:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they are usually at the bottom of the box\Nfull of self-hatred, hopelessness, despair
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.38,0:49:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,regret, despondency\Nand we see that the energy field down here
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.70,0:49:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of apathy, of hopelessness and despair\Nis one in which the person cannot help themself
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.70,0:49:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and hopeless means just that\Nand a friend of mine
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.70,0:50:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,who was president of the county bar association\Nliterally died of starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.70,0:50:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,alone in a rooming house\Naddicted to a combination of valium and alcohol
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.70,0:50:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,never even picked up the phone\Nto call anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.83,0:50:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,literally died of starvation\Na person of that caliber
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.83,0:50:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,with thousands of friends\Nall of whom would have dropped anything
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.83,0:50:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to come and help him\Nhopeless means just that means that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.83,0:50:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no point in making the phone call\Nbecause there is no hope
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.83,0:50:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that hopelessness about one's condition\Nwhich often expresses itself as
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.96,0:50:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,my case is different\Nmy case is different
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.96,0:50:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning you may well recover from this\Nbut my case is hopeless
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.96,0:50:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out of this apathy, this hopelessness\Nin which God is dead
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.96,0:50:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what can we do for the person\Nbecause the process over here in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.96,0:50:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of loss of energy\Nthe person is de-energized
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.96,0:50:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the woman who is rocking back and forth\Nin her rocking chair
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.96,0:50:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,staring out the window blankly\Nall we can do is pour energy into that person
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.12,0:51:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,reason doesn't have any effect\Nwe saw that when the telegram
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.12,0:51:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,from the state department came\Nand said it was a mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.12,0:51:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that her energy field didn't change\Nshe kept right on rocking back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.12,0:51:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and staring out the window\Nso the answer is to pour energy
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.12,0:51:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,into that person\Nby our concern
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.12,0:51:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by our lovingness\Nby our physical presence
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.12,0:51:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,through nutrition\Nin every possible way
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.12,0:51:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we pour energy into that person\Nand get them up to the next energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.47,0:51:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,called grief\Ngrief
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.47,0:51:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,grief has to do with the past\Nand next what the person will experience
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.47,0:51:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,when they come out of the shock\Nthey come in a blank shock like state
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.47,0:51:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is they will begin to cry\Nbegin to regret
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.47,0:51:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss that all this addiction has cost them\Nregret
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.47,0:51:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling self-pity\Nsorrow for the fact that they are
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.47,0:51:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in a rehabilitation place\Nor they are in the space they are in life
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.47,0:51:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they are very sad about life\Nsad about their addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.56,0:51:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they feel completely neglected by God\Nand so there is this spirited state
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.56,0:52:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,spirit being that willingness\Nthe aliveness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.56,0:52:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of life itself\Nso this regret about the past
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.56,0:52:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we move the person's energy field up\Nand we move them up
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.56,0:52:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next energy field\Nwhich is one of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.56,0:52:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at this point the person begins to fear the addiction\Nworry and anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.56,0:52:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,fear has to do with the future\Nthey are no longer in the inflated state of denial
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.56,0:52:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on the contrary they are deflated\Nthe world looks frightening
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.56,0:52:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and they perhaps feel that God is punishing them\Nfor their past sins
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.56,0:52:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so they are misinterpreting the addiction now\Nas a punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.56,0:52:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and they are fearing a punishment\Nof more punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.56,0:52:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and further loss in the future\Nbut the energy of each thing can move up
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.98,0:52:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to the energy of the next\Nand so we move the person out of the fear of the addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.98,0:52:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,into the desiring for something better\Ndesiring something other than being victim
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.98,0:52:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the wanting this\Nthe craving this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.98,0:53:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the wanting to move into something better for yourself\Nand move them up to anger
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.98,0:53:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,anger as we said has a lot of useful energy in it\Nnot the form of anger
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.11,0:53:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not the form of anger itself\Nbut the energy of anger
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.11,0:53:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the person then becomes angry\Nover their predicament in life
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.11,0:53:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,angry over being victim\Nthis anger then
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.59,0:53:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw that we see it used in society\Nin a constructive way
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.59,0:53:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw the way we see the way minority groups\Nget angry over the injustices
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.59,0:53:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of their social position\Nand use the energy of that anger
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.59,0:53:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to mobilize social forces\Nand move up to pride
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.59,0:53:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in doing something about it\Nto take action
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.59,0:53:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to take action\Nto begin to move up into
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.59,0:53:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,caring for oneself\Ncaring for one's position
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.59,0:53:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and moving up to the next energy field of courage\Ncourage is crucial in the addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.00,0:53:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to tell the truth\Nand so we see the powerful effect then
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.00,0:54:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that the first step has\Nthe admission that we're powerless over alcohol or drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.00,0:54:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,now allows us to face\Ncope, handle
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.00,0:54:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and be appropriate\Nwe become re-empowered
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.00,0:54:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we now see the world\Nas an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.00,0:54:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the first time we have an open mind\Ntruth has a way
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.00,0:54:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to enter our mind\Nso we move the person
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.00,0:54:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we utilize the pride\Nto move the person up in the courage
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.00,0:54:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to look at the facts\Nand in looking at the facts
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.00,0:54:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,encouraging them to move up to the next position\Nwhich is letting go, resisting the facts
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.00,0:54:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be released from that resistance\Nso they can begin to view the world as an okay place
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.00,0:54:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to utilize and experience their own freedom\Nfreedom to explore, to expand
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.00,0:54:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and move them up to the willingness then\Nto say yes in this exploration
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.36,0:54:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to join it, to agree, to align with it\Nand they join their intention
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.36,0:54:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so they begin to see\Nthe whole rehabilitative process
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.36,0:55:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world in which it is happening\Nas friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.36,0:55:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they begin to see Alcoholics Anonymous, let's say\Nas promising and hopeful
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.36,0:55:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that perhaps they will recover\Nand move them up into acceptance then
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.36,0:55:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a very powerful energy field\Nwhere you are beginning to see
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.36,0:55:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have the power to make these decisions\Nthe confidence, the feeling of adequacy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.36,0:55:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the transformation that comes about\Nand now the experiencing that the world is harmonious
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.36,0:55:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it is on the one hand presented you with a problem\Non the other hand it is harmonious
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.36,0:55:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in that it also provides you with the answer\Nthat which is a merciful God provides you with solutions
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.36,0:55:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so although you may have an addiction\Nyou find that there are hundreds of thousands of people around
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.36,0:55:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,who have found the answers\Nwho are only too willing to help you with this
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.36,0:55:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and now the world begins to look\Nfriendly, harmonious, merciful, helpful, hopeful
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.36,0:55:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and with acceptance and the letting go of the resistance\Nand the letting go of denial
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.80,0:56:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we move into an energy field of lovingness\Nwhere the person then commits themself
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.80,0:56:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to an energy field which is healing\Nby joining one of the 12 step groups
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.80,0:56:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the person's willingness to align with it\Ntheir willingness to accept it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.28,0:56:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so through that willingness then comes acceptance\Nand the acceptance of the truth about this
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.28,0:56:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is that we need to be in an energy field\Nwhich is nurturing, supportive and understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.28,0:56:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which is unconditionally loving\Nmove the person into that energy field then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.83,0:56:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and we know that they are in a safe space\Nto remain aligned with that then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.83,0:56:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is to ensure one's survival\Nand with that experience comes the joyfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.96,0:56:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of the experience of an inner serenity\Nthe beginning to see the perfection and the oneness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.96,0:56:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of the energy field which you are now part and parcel of\Nwas the willingness to tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.18,0:57:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,moving us up through this very critical level\Nthe first step, our willingness to admit
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.18,0:57:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that we were powerless over alcohol and drugs\Nthat was making our life unmanageable
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.18,0:57:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the second step then becomes very significant\Nit says in all of the 12 step groups
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.18,0:57:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the second step was the restoring us to sanity\Nby some power greater than ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.18,0:57:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the intuitive understanding of the ego\Nof the small self
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.18,0:57:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that it will take something with much greater power\Nthan its smallness to handle this problem
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.18,0:57:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we look at bliss and we see that the energy field of that\Nstarting at about 500 and running all the way up to 600
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.18,0:57:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is like a powerful electromagnet pulling one\Nback into wanting to re-experience
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.18,0:57:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that experience in consciousness\Nand therefore to handle it something of an equal dimension
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.18,0:57:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of an equal dimension will be needed to handle it\Nso the second step is really the intuitive knowing of that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.18,0:58:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that something greater than the ego\Nthe limited small self
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.18,0:58:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to be needed to handle the attraction\Nof such a powerful energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.18,0:58:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the third step then is the decision that comes out of that\Nthe surrendering
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.18,0:58:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the third step is one of surrender\Nturning the willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.18,0:58:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to turn one's life\Nover to God as one understands him
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.18,0:58:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of willingness\Njust out of willingness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.18,0:58:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you see\Nthat the God of alcoholics
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.18,0:58:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of one's own understanding\Nis already a friendly, promising and hopeful God
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.18,0:58:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,using the example of the people\Nthat one sees who have done this
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.18,0:58:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning willingness to be trusting\Nthe beginning elements of faith
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.18,0:58:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and so the third step then\Nthe step of deep surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.18,0:58:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,really moves one into this alignment\Nthis energy field of 500 and over
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.79,0:58:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the rest of the steps now make sense\Nof course from the viewpoint of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.79,0:59:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as we've looked at it\Nthe fourth step says
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.79,0:59:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that we looked within the box\Nto find out
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.79,0:59:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what was in the box\Nin our own particular case
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.79,0:59:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,took a fearless moral inventory\Nthe willingness to look at all that was negative in our life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.79,0:59:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,our willingness to own that\Nand then in the fifth step
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.79,0:59:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a very healing step\Nadmit to ourself, to God
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.79,0:59:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and to another human being\Nthe exact nature of that which we discovered within the box
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.79,0:59:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,by doing that\Nwe change the energy field of it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.79,0:59:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we take the charge off of it\Nwe take the negativity off of it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.79,0:59:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so that now the same event\Nalthough it hasn't changed in history
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.79,0:59:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the way we are holding it has changed\Nso that which had the capacity to corrode
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.79,0:59:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and destroy us before\Nis now rendered inoperative
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.79,0:59:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,see Bill Wilson used to say\Nthat the correct attitude about the past
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.79,1:00:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is a decent regret\Na decent regret
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.79,1:00:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,one may regret it\Nbut that's quite a bit different
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.79,1:00:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,than self-hatred leading to self-destruction\Ninstead one comes from the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.98,1:00:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill used to say\NAA is the language of the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.98,1:00:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the heart\Nwith its humor
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.98,1:00:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with its lightness\Nto look at the past
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.98,1:00:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and the willingness to heal it\Nthe healing then comes out of the step five
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.68,1:00:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it's expressed in steps six through nine\Nwhich are really
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.68,1:00:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the reparative steps\Nthose are steps in which
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.68,1:00:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the person takes responsibility\Nto actually do something in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.68,1:00:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to repair any damage that is repairable\Nto mend whatever fences can be mended
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.68,1:00:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it's not just a mental intellectual exercise\Nso that it becomes real
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.68,1:00:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and relieves all the guilt\Nabout what one has done in the past
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.68,1:00:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to one's best ability\None goes back into the world
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.68,1:00:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and tries to repair\Nthe damages that have been done
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.68,1:01:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to the degree that they're repairable\Nstep ten then
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.29,1:01:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,says that this way of life\Nof taking responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.29,1:01:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for the content of our own consciousness\Nthe willingness to clean it up
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.29,1:01:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that this became our way of life\Nand we began to do this on a daily basis
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.42,1:01:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,on a daily basis\Nwe looked within the box
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.42,1:01:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to see what had gone wrong\Nwhat was out
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.42,1:01:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what was lacking in integrity\Nwhere could we have done better
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.42,1:01:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,where could we have been more loving\Nso the owning then of the process
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.42,1:01:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual progress\Nour commitment to that as a way of life
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.42,1:01:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is step ten\Nstep eleven is interesting then
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.58,1:01:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because it says\Nwhat it says is if we do steps one through ten
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.58,1:01:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,if we make that our lifestyle\Nthat we will reconnect with something
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.58,1:01:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that we sought in the first place\Nthrough drugs and alcohol
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.58,1:02:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it says sought through prayer and meditation\Nto increase our conscious contact with God
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.58,1:02:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as we understood\Nasking only for his will for us
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.58,1:02:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and the power to carry it out\Nsee loving doesn't say
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.58,1:02:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we began\Nit said it already happened
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.58,1:02:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it said that when we committed ourselves to loving this\Nas a lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.58,1:02:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we reconnected\Nwe began to reconnect through the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.58,1:02:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because that which is divine\Nthat which is God
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.58,1:02:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is love\Nare all the same thing are they not
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.58,1:02:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as we committed to loving this\Nas our style and way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.58,1:02:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to the best of our ability\Nwe began to reconnect with some
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.58,1:02:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,rock like inner experience\Nwhich was similar to that which we sought in the first place
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.22,1:02:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,then step twelve gives away\Nwhat the whole addictive process is about
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.22,1:02:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what its whole nature is in the field of consciousness\Nstep twelve says
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.22,1:02:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,having become conscious\Nas a result of this total experience
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.22,1:02:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the language of the twelfth step is\Nhaving had a spiritual awakening
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.32,1:03:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,having become conscious\Nhaving had a spiritual awakening
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.32,1:03:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of the entire addictive experience\Nwe carried this message to others
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.32,1:03:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and expressed it in our entire life\Nso the twelfth step tells us then
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.32,1:03:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what the whole purpose of the addictive process was\Nit was to awaken us
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.32,1:03:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it was to move us\Nfrom one level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.32,1:03:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to another\Nfrom being asleep and unaware
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.32,1:03:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to being awake and conscious\Nand aware and responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.32,1:03:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from being unconscious and irresponsible\Nfrom being helpless victim
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.32,1:03:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to owning ourselves as the source\Nand being responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.32,1:03:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for the happiness within our life\Nto stop putting it out there
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.89,1:03:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop saying that the source of happiness\Nis outside of myself
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.89,1:03:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize that the source of my happiness\Nis the same as the source of my life
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.89,1:03:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to own myself irresponsibly\Nas a spiritually aware person
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.92,1:03:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so now we have a different context\Nin which the whole addictive process
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.92,1:04:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a movement of advancing and increasing\Nconsciousness and awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.92,1:04:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so that alcoholism and drugs then\Nrequire that a person become more awake
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.92,1:04:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to survive\Nand here we have a disease that is
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.92,1:04:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively fatal\Nand that the only way to recover from the illness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.92,1:04:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is to become progressively spiritually aware\Nprogressively more conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.92,1:04:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so that life itself\Ndepends on becoming conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.92,1:04:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a major self confrontation\Nsomething that our higher self
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.92,1:04:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,has picked for us\Nthat will force us to grow
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.92,1:04:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's no turning back\Nthere's no reprogramming the brain cells
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.92,1:04:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,once they're programmed\Nthere's not enough room on the tightrope
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.92,1:04:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn around and change one's mind\Nand once one is into the addictive
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.92,1:04:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,alcoholic process\Nthere is no turning back
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.92,1:04:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there is only the confront\Nwith owning the truth about oneself
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.92,1:04:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and total recovery depends on\Naccepting that process
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.92,1:05:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,moving joyfully into it\Nbeing grateful
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.92,1:05:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you hear now\Nand you understand why
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.92,1:05:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you hear speakers at meetings of AA for instance say\Nthat they're grateful they're an alcoholic
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.92,1:05:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to the newcomer this sounds indeed like madness\Ngrateful?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.92,1:05:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,how could one be grateful?\Nbecause they're coming from self hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.92,1:05:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and guilt about this thing\Nhow could one be grateful?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.96,1:05:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,how could one be grateful\Nthat one has become addicted or an alcoholic
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.96,1:05:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because that forced us to grow\Nit forced us to become conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.96,1:05:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it forced us to become aware\Nwe become grateful to the process
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.96,1:05:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at first resenting it\Nat first resisting it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.96,1:05:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then actually accepting it\Nthen agreeing with it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.96,1:05:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then beginning to love\Nthen experiencing joy
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.96,1:05:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then achieving that state called serenity\Nthe inner knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.96,1:05:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that this was your destiny\Nthis was your way of doing it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.96,1:05:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the way that you chose\Nit's okay
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.96,1:06:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's wonderful\Nit's sort of an awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.96,1:06:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that you never could have reached this understanding\Nany other way
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.96,1:06:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,some people just have to experience it this way\Nfor those who did
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.96,1:06:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,great gratitude comes about\Nand a greater understanding of the nature of consciousness itself
